        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: Add Codex rate-limit reset credits to menu card",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nShow available Codex rate-limit reset credits and the next usable credit expiry in the app and CLI for signed-in OAuth accounts.\n\nFixes #1633.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Fetch the account-scoped reset-credit endpoint as bounded, best-effort OAuth enrichment with a 4-second timeout.\n- Preserve positive reset-credit results even when the usage response has no rate-limit windows; empty reset-credit responses still surface missing usage.\n- Render reset counts and expiry in menu cards and `codexbar usage`, respecting optional-usage and reset-time preferences.\n- Ignore stale expired credits when selecting the next expiry.\n- Add all 21 app localizations, height/recycling fingerprints, changelog credit, and focused request/parser/model/CLI regressions.\n- Keep required usage authoritative and avoid sibling `async let` lifetime hazards.\n\n## Verification\n\nExact head: `57170e008edbbfaa615802c44486251e6a2b3c26`\n\n- `swift test --filter 'CodexOAuthTests|CodexRateLimitResetCreditsTests|CodexResetCreditsMenuCardTests|CLISnapshotTests|MenuCardHeightFingerprintTests'` (64 tests)\n- `make check`\n- Full-branch autoreview: no actionable findings\n- Live OAuth CLI: exit 0, OAuth source, no provider error, two available reset credits returned\n- Direct account-scoped endpoint: HTTP 200 with the expected credit schema\n- Fresh release package built and launched; local menu screenshot was blocked by the macOS app-data privacy prompt, which was left untouched\n\n## Screenshot\n\n<img width=\"290\" height=\"358\" alt=\"Codex reset credits in the usage card\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7c30671f-8940-4b84-84f7-50dfd292ed19\" />\n",
